  - Autonomous Knowledge Evolution: Cognitive engines will autonomously
    discover, optimize, and share execution templates across safe, verified
    network channels.

PART XXX: Appendices

30.1 Domain Definition Grammar (EBNF Specification)

domain_definition ::= "domain" identifier "{" { domain_element } "}"
domain_element    ::= type_definition | constant_definition | action_definition | compound_task

type_definition   ::= "type" identifier [ ":" identifier ] ";"
constant_definition::= "const" identifier ":" identifier ";"

action_definition ::= "action" identifier "(" [ parameter_list ] ")" "{" action_body "}"
action_body       ::= [ precondition_block ] [ effect_block ]
precondition_block::= "preconditions" ":" logical_expression ";"
effect_block      ::= "effects" ":" logical_expression ";"

compound_task     ::= "task" identifier "(" [ parameter_list ] ")" "{" task_body "}"
task_body         ::= "methods" ":" { method_definition }
method_definition ::= "method" identifier "{" method_body "}"
method_body       ::= [ precondition_block ] "subtasks" ":" task_list ";"

parameter_list    ::= parameter { "," parameter }
parameter         ::= identifier ":" identifier
task_list         ::= task_invocation { "," task_invocation }
task_invocation   ::= identifier "(" [ argument_list ] ")"

30.2 Planning Domain Definition Sample (CASPER Domain Language)

domain developer_career_management {
    type user_profile;
    type resume_file : file;
    type web_session : network_resource;

    task acquire_backend_job(user: user_profile) {
        methods:
            method apply_via_job_boards {
                preconditions:
                    user.has_verified_resume == true;
                subtasks:
                    open_job_portal_session(user),
                    scrape_matching_roles(user),
                    dispatch_applications_loop(user);
            }
            
            method build_resume_first {
                preconditions:
                    user.has_verified_resume == false;
                subtasks:
                    compile_resume_from_profile(user),
                    acquire_backend_job(user);
            }
    }

    action compile_resume_from_profile(user: user_profile) {
        preconditions:
            user.has_completed_projects == true;
        effects:
            user.has_verified_resume = true;
    }
}

30.3 Glossary of Technical Terms

  - Active Inference: A mathematical framework modeling cognition as the
    minimization of variational free energy through state updates and
    environmental actions.
  - Arc Consistency (AC-3): An algorithm used to prune invalid domains in
    Constraint Satisfaction Problems, optimizing backtracking search
    performance.
  - Causal Intervention: Direct manipulation of variable states within
    structural causal models using do-calculus to predict results.
  - Expected Free Energy (G): A variational metric used in active inference to
    select optimal, goal-seeking policies over a temporal horizon.
  - Hierarchical Task Network (HTN): A planning paradigm that decomposes
    compound tasks recursively into chains of primitive operations.
  - Task State Block (TSB): A structured, verifiable data packet tracking active
    operational variables, variables, and progress metrics for a task.
  - Variational Free Energy (\mathcal{F}): A mathematical bound measuring
    internal model error, minimized through belief state updates.
